Netflix User Behavior & Revenue Analysis

📌 Project Overview
Understanding user behavior is essential for subscription-based streaming platforms to improve customer engagement, optimize pricing strategies, and maximize revenue. This project analyzes Netflix user demographics, subscription plans, device preferences, and monthly revenue to identify patterns that influence platform performance.

Using the Netflix Userbase Dataset, this project performs comprehensive Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA), data visualization, descriptive statistics, and statistical hypothesis testing to uncover relationships between user characteristics and monthly revenue.

🎯 Objectives
Analyze Netflix user demographics and subscription patterns.
Perform exploratory data analysis (EDA).
Visualize user distribution across countries, devices, and subscription plans.
Examine monthly revenue trends.
Identify relationships between customer attributes and revenue.
Perform statistical hypothesis testing to validate observed patterns.

📊 Dataset

Dataset: Netflix Userbase Dataset

The dataset contains user information related to Netflix subscriptions.

